Package: R_course_exam2
Type: Package
Title: Simple Semantic Text Analysis for Positive and Negative Word Detection
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Robert Tonoian
Maintainer: Robert Tonoian <tonoiainrk@gmail.com>
Description: A lightweight package developed for the HT2025 Intermediate R Programming Course group exam. 
    It provides functions to preprocess text, match words against semantic dictionaries 
    with optional wildcard support, and summarise positive and negative sentiment in a document.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Depends: R (>= 4.3)
Imports:
    stringr
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
